[V: RH3] D | C D E E | (E D) D D | G F E D | D C B, | % % A2: diatonic, contrary to A1 where possible. Stays below A1 always. % Bar1: G, A, B, C (ascending in thirds below A1 roughly — G3 A3 B3 C4) %   A1=C D E E; A2=G, A, B, C → A2 is a fifth/sixth below. This opens nicely. % Bar2: C B, B, A, (descent) % Bar3: D D C B, (gentle descent in contrary motion to A1's descent... actually A1 descends, %         A2 should ascend for contrary: B, C D E → but must stay below A1) %   A1 bar3: G F E D. For contrary: A2 could go B, B, C D. That's below A1. ✓ % Bar4: G, F, G, (3 beats; approach from below to root) F | B, C D D | D3 E | D E F F | A G G | % % A2 bar5: G, A, B, B, (third below A1 roughly; G3 A3 B3 B3) % A2 bar6: A,3 B, (A3 dotted-half + B3; third below A1's D4; ✓ diatonic) % A2 bar7: B, C D D (ascending — A2 follows A1 more closely here for blend) %   Actually A2 should be below A1: A1=D E F F, A2 stay below: B, C D D ✓ (B3 C4 D4 D4, A1=D4 E4 F#4 F#4) % A2 bar8: F E E (3 beats; F#4 E4 E4 — thirds below A1's A4 G4 G4 → F#4 E4 E4 ✓; F written=F# ✓) % Pickup D = D4 ✓ E | G F E D | (D C) B, B, | B, C D E | D C B, |] % % A2 bar9: D D C B, (A2 below A1: D4 D4 C4 B3 — A1=G F E D; A2 must be below: D D C B, %   but A1=G4 F#4 E4 D4 and A2=D4 D4 C4 B3 — at bars 9-10 A2 is below A1 ✓ %   But A2=D4 is same as A1=D4 on beat4 bar9 — allowed (pair unison) ✓) % A2 bar10: B, A, G, G, (B3 A3 G3 G3 — stepwise; below A1's D4 C4 B3 B3 ✓) % A2 bar11: G, A, B, C (ascending, mirrors A1 in contrary... A1 ascends B3→E4, A2 G3→C4 same direction) %   For contrary: A2 should descend while A1 ascends. A2 bar11: D C B, A, (D4 C4 B3 A3 — descending) %   But must stay below A1 (B3 C4 D4 E4): A2=D4 C4 B3 A3 — A2 beat1=D4=A1 beat1=B3: D4>B3, A2>A1! Voice cross! %   Fix: A2 bar11: G, A, B, C (G3 A3 B3 C4 — ascending, stays below A1 ✓ since A1=B3 C4 D4 E4 and A2=G3 A3 B3 C4 ✓) % A2 bar12: B, A, G, (3 beats; B3 A3 G3 — stepwise descent to tonic; below A1's D4 C4 B3: wait bar12 A1=D C B, → B3... A2 bar12