[V: RH4] B, | G, A, B, C | (C B,) B, A, | B, B, C D | G, F, G, | % % T1 written in 8vb treble (sounds an octave lower than written). % Written pitch = concert pitch + octave. % Target concert: D3-G4 range for comfortable tenor. % Written: D4-G5 (comfortable T1 range). % % T1 follows original tenor harmony (S2V1) recomposed as melodic line. % Original S2V1 pickup: D4 → written D5... actually let me use written octave consistently: %   Concert B3 = written B4, Concert D4 = written D5 — getting high. %   Better: Concert D3 = written D4, Concert G3 = written G4. %   So "written D" in the 8vb treble voice = concert D3, "written B" = concert B3. %   Using ABC in 8vb treble staff: D = concert D3, B = concert B3, c = concert C4, g = concert G4. % % Pickup: D (concert D3, comfortable opening) % Bar1: D E F G (ascending D3-G3, smooth and independent of SSAA) % Bar2: G G F E (descent; T1=G3 under bar2's C5 in S1 — fine spacing) % Bar3: B A F G (B3 A3 F#3 G3 — follows original tenor D D D F# shape, diatonic) %   Original S2V1 bar3: D D D F, → concert D4 D4 D4 F#3... for T1 line: B A F G (B3 A3 F#3 G3) % Bar4: D E D (3 beats; D3 E3 D3 — gentle motion at fermata) %   Original S2V1 bar4: (G,/F,/ G,) A, → G3 F#3 G3 A3; for T1: D E D (3 beats) D | G, A, B, B, | A,3 B, | B, C D D | F E E | % % T1 bar5: D E F G (D3→G3 ascending, mirrors bar1 — unifying motif) %   Original S2V1: D, E,/F,/ G, G, → D3 E3-F#3(8ths) G3 G3; T1: D E F G written ✓ % T1 bar6: c3 B (C4 dotted-half + B3 — top of comfortable T1 range; bar6 is climax of sec.2) %   D chord: D F# A C — C4 (7th) is a good inner voice here. %   Original S2V1 bar6: F,3 B, → F#3 dotted-half + B3; T1: c3 B (climax) ✓ % T1 bar7: B c d E (B3 C4 D4 E3... wait — need to stay within range and avoid voice cross) %   T1 bar7: let's use B c d e (B3 C4 D4 E4 — ascending; written in 8vb: B c d e ✓) %   Check against A2 bar7=B, C D D (B3 C4 D4 D4 concert) — T1 and A2 share pitches %   A2-T1 cross-choir unison is explicitly permitted. ✓ % T1 bar8: e d d (3 beats; E4 D4 D4 concert — written e d d in 8vb; climactic bar) %   Original S2V1 bar8: A,/B,/C/D/ E → A3-B3-C4-D4-E4; T1: e d d ✓ (stepwise descent after climb) % Pickup F (written) = F#3 concert ✓ C | D D C B, | (B, A,) G, G, | G, A, B, C | B, A, G, |] % % T1 written in 8vb treble. Concert range B2-G4; written B3-G5. % Pickup: E (written E4 = sounds E3 ✓) % T1 bar9: d c d B (written; sounds D4 C4 D4 B3 — melodic echo of S1's d d A B, displaced) %   This creates the canonic imitation: T1 echoes S1 a beat later rhythmically. %   But in homophony (same rhythm) it's harmonic support, not true canon. %   For the "canonic echo" texture, T1 could have a 2-beat displacement... %   but strict canon is complex in ABC. Instead, give T1 a strong independent melodic line. %   Original S2V1 bar9: D/C/ B, ^C F, → D4 C4 C#4 F#3; remove ^C → D4 C4 C4 F#3 = D C C F (written) ✓ %   T1: d c c F (D4 C4 C4 F#3 concert; written d c c F ✓; all diatonic ✓) %   Actually use: d c B A (D4 C4 B3 A3 — smooth descending, independent of S1) ✓ % T1 bar10: B2 A D (written B3(half) + A3 + D3; 4 beats: B B A D... wait 4 beats) %   Bar10 has 4 beats. B2=half(2beats)+A+D = 4 beats ✓ %   Original S2V1 bar10: B,2 B, B, → B3 B3 B3 B3 (4 beats); T1: B2 A D ✓ (varied) % T1 bar11: B c d e (ascending line toward climax; written B3 C4 D4 E4 concert ✓) %   Original S2V1 bar11: B,/C/ B,/A,/ G, G, → B3-C4-B3-A3-G3-G3; T1: B c d e for climax ✓ % T1 bar12: e d B (3 beats; E4 D4 B3 concert — stepwise descent to tonic chord tone; written e d B ✓) %   Original S2V1 bar12: E A,/B,/ B, → E4 A3-B3-B3; T1: e d B ✓
[V: LH1] D | D E F G | (G G) F E | B A F G | D E D | % % T2 harmonizes a third below T1 (written), diatonic. % Pickup: B, (concert B2, written B3 in 8vb treble → but B, in ABC = B3 written... %   In ABC standard: B = B4, B, = B3. In 8vb treble clef the written B4 sounds B3. %   So written "B" (no comma) in [V:5/6] = sounds B3. Written "B," = sounds B2. ✓ %   T2 pickup: G (written G4 sounds G3, a third below T1's written D(sounds D3)) %   Wait: T1 pickup written D sounds D3; T2 a third below concert = B2 = written B, in 8vb. %   Use B, for T2 pickup (concert B2, written B3 in 8vb = ABC "B,") % % Bar1: B, C D E (third below T1: D→B, E→C, F#→D, G→E — written, diatonic) ✓ % Bar2: E E D C (third below T1: G→E, G→E, F#→D, E→C) % Bar3: G F D E (third below: B→G, A→F#, F#→D, G→E) % Bar4: B, C B, (3 beats; third below T1: D→B, E→C, D→B) F | D E F G | c3 B | B c d e | e d d | % % T2 bar5: B, C D D (third below T1: D→B, E→C, F#→D, G→E... third below G is E; use B,C D E) %   Thirds below: D→B, E→C, F→D, G→E → B, C D E ✓ (written, diatonic) %   But D D in T1 bar5 → T2: B, B, — avoid T2 repeating a note while T1 moves %   Use B, C D E (third below each T1 note: D B→ wait D-B is a third, E-C is a third, F#-D is a third, G-E is a third ✓) % T2 bar6: A,3 G, (A3 G3 dotted-half... third below T1's c=C4: A3; then below B3: G3 ✓) % T2 bar7: G A B c (third below T1 B c d e: G A B c ✓ written; all diatonic ✓) % T2 bar8: c B B (3 beats; third below T1's e d d: c B... wait third below E=C, D=B ✓) % Pickup D (written) = D3 concert ✓ E | d c B A | B2 A D | B c d e | e d B |] % % T2 a third below T1 (written), diatonic. % Pickup: C (written C4 = sounds C3) % T2 bar9: B A G F (third below T1 d c B A: B A G F# → B A G F ✓; F=F# in key ✓) % T2 bar10: G2 F B, (third below T1: B→G, A→F#→F, D→B; G2(half)+F+B, = 4 beats ✓) % T2 bar11: G A B c (third below T1 B c d e: G A B c ✓) % T2 bar12: c B G (3 beats; third below T1 e d B: c B G ✓)
