[V: LH4] G,, | C,/B,,/ A,, G,,3/2 F,,/ | (E,, F,,) G,, E,, | B,,/A,,/ B,,/C,/ D,/C,/ B,, | E,,2 D,, | % % ============================================================ % SECTION 2  (1-beat pickup + bars 5–8, last bar = 3 beats) % % Texture: Full 8-voice block homophony. All voices move together % (syllabic, hymn-style). Maximum weight and corporate sound. % % Bar 5: G A B B   (S1) % Harmony: G | Am | Bm | Bm % % Bar 6: A3 B   = A dotted-half + B quarter = 4 beats % Harmony: D  (long)  | G % % Bar 7: G A B/c/ d   (same shape as bar 1) % Harmony: G | Am | Bm | G % % Bar 8 (3 beats): c2 B % Harmony: C | G fermata % ============================================================ % % Pickup: S1=D4. Original S1V2 pickup=A,3... that's A3. Section 2 pickups: %   S1=D4, S2=A3(=A,), A1=F#4(=F), A2=D4(=D), T1=F#(written,=F#3sounding), %   T2=D(written,=D3sounding), Bar=C,(C3), B1=C,,(C2) %   Note: original S2V1 pickup = F,/E,/ (two eighths); simplify to F, (quarter) C,, | B,,/A,,/ B,,/C,/ D,,/C,,/ B,,, | D,,3 E,, | E,, F,, G,, A,, | A,, G,, E,, | % % ============================================================ % SECTION 3  (1-beat pickup + bars 9–12, last bar = 3 beats) % % Texture: Bars 9-10 canonic — SSAA have the melody, TTBB echo % the same phrase a half-bar later in imitation (not strict canon, % but rhythmically displaced echo). Bars 11-12 stretto with all % voices converging on the final cadence in full homophony. % % Bar 9: d d A B   (S1) % Harmony: G | D | Am | G/B % (Original has spacer rests: d y d A y B — treat as d d A B in 4/4) % % Bar 10: G2 F D   = G half + F quarter + D quarter = 4 beats % (The original =D is the D on beat 4 of bar 10, %  which also serves as a pickup into bar 11 by feel, but is metrically beat 4.) % Harmony: G | G | D7 | D % % Bar 11: G A B c   (S1) % Harmony: G | Am | Bm | C % % Bar 12 (3 beats): B A G   — final cadential resolution % Harmony: Bm | Am | G % % The  /  markers in the original indicate a repeated % final section for performance; this arrangement writes it out once. % ============================================================ % % Pickup: B (S1=B4, the pickup into section 3) % Original S1V2 pickup: =G (G4, natural — already diatonic ✓) E,, | F,,/G,,/ G,,/F,,/ E,,/D,,/ C,, | E,,/F,,/ G,,/A,,/ B,, B,, | E,, F,, G,, E,, | C,, D,, G,,, |] W: 6. My loved ones, rest securely, For God this night will surely W: From peril guard your heads. Sweet slumbers may He send you W: And bid His hosts attend you And through the night watch o'er your beds.
